here the constructor does not lock https://github.com/ARMmbed/mbed-os/blob/master/drivers/DigitalInOut.h#L41 however there are many chips where the actions in the constructor would be race conditions if interrupted by a context switch or ISR. What exactly is so special about the constructor that it does not need to lock?

```
//one thread
DigitalInOut pin1(/*some pin*/);

//other thread
DigitalInOut pin2(/*other pin*/); //if context switch somes at the right time this is race condition

//maybe in an ISR
pin1.input(); //if this interrupts the constructor of pin2 then race condition
```

Currently, IAR requires that device has a CMSIS pack to find the debug interface. With that assumption, if a debug interface cannot be found, it defaults to CMSIS-DAP. This change will mean that the default CMSIS-DAP is also used when there is not CMSIS pack at all. 

Fixes #3286

